id: pm-tgq6
title: "Flaky Windows nightly: stale-cleanup lock test intermittently misses the mocked owner-write failure (GH-427)"
description: "Nightly Validation windows-latest/Node 24 failed 2026-07-05 (run 28733397917) on core-item-lock-coverage.spec.ts 'keeps stale cleanup busy and cleans up when stale cleanup owner write fails': expected [AsyncFunction] to be null, i.e. acquireStaleCleanupGate succeeded because the vi.spyOn(fs.writeFile) interception (String(targetPath) === ownerPath) never fired. Passed on 2026-07-04 and 2026-07-06 nightlies - intermittent, Windows-only. The separate 2026-07-04 nightly failures (EPERM vs EACCES/EISDIR errno assumptions in restore-command and history-rewrite specs) are already fixed on main via stringMatching(/^(EACCES|EPERM)$/)."
type: Issue
