body: "Hypotheses to check when reproducing: (1) owner.json written through a different path spelling or a writeFileAtomic temp name so the strict equality path guard misses; (2) leftover gate directory state from a sibling test; (3) race between gate mkdir and owner write cleanup on slower Windows runners.\n\nSuggested hardening: match on path.basename/endsWith instead of strict full-path equality, or normalize both sides with path.resolve; assert gate dir is absent before starting.\n\nEvidence: GH issue #427, failed run https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/actions/runs/28733397917 (2026-07-05), green runs 2026-07-04 (this test) and 2026-07-06 (all)."
